## Pre-Completion Checks

> Run these before marking any task complete, regardless of what the task
> was. These catch the specific class of mistake that passes tests and
> lint but still shouldn't ship.

```bash
# No debug logging left behind
grep -rn "console\.\(log\|debug\)" src/

# No suppressed type errors without explanation
grep -rn "@ts-expect-error\|@ts-ignore" src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.vue" -A1
# Every match must have an inline comment on the same or next line
# explaining WHY the suppression is safe. A suppression with no reasoning
# is a red flag — it likely means a real API mismatch was hidden rather
# than fixed. Compile-time suppression does not prevent a runtime crash;
# if the underlying pattern is wrong, the browser will still fail even
# though the type checker is now quiet.

# No duplicate imports from the same module in one file
# (manual check or lint rule if your linter supports it)
```

