## Post-Release Maintenance

> Consider adding these once a project reaches v1 and is deployed — not
> before. Introducing them earlier is premature process for a project still
> finding its shape.

- Automated dependency updates (Renovate or Dependabot) with CI gating any auto-PR
- Scheduled Lighthouse/Unlighthouse run against the deployed URL, flagging
  regressions below an agreed threshold (Accessibility and Best Practices
  matter most; treat SEO score as informational for a portfolio-scale project)
- Bundle-size tracking across builds if the project is sensitive to load time

---

## Skill Update Protocol

When a new verified pattern is discovered during development, the Reviewer
role adds it to the relevant stack-pattern doc with a one-line explanation
of why it was added and the date. The Orchestrator confirms the addition
is consistent with AGENTS.md before committing.

---

## Graceful Fallback

If the primary model is unavailable or out of tokens, every command in this
file works identically regardless of which model is active. Governance in
AGENTS.md is model-agnostic. `docs/architecture.md` is the source of truth
— a fallback model does not need to remember anything, only read the files.

